DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(79)90017-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393279900175
AB  - This paper raises two criticisms with respect to the result advanced by Ando and Shell according to which money demand should be independent from wealth variations. First, it is shown that, even within the assumptions of the Ando and Shell model, there is in general a range of wealth variation over which money balances respond positively to wealth. Second, the result of those authors is criticized on the basis that it essentially derives from an inadequate comparative statics experiment on asset demands.
